byline.contributor: Nicola Clark contributed reporting from Paris.

abstract: Russian investigators say strong winds may have caused jetliner from Dubai, United Arab Emirates, to crash while attempting to land near city of Rostov-on-Don, killing all 55 passengers and seven crew members on board.

headline.print_headline: Strong Wind May Have Caused Fatal Plane Crash in Russia, Investigators Say
headline.main: Wind Given as Possible Cause of Fatal Plane Crash in Russia

snippet: All 55 passengers and seven crew members died when a United Arab Emirates plane crashed in the southern city of Rostov-on-Don, Russian officials said.
lead_paragraph: All 55 passengers and seven crew members died when a United Arab Emirates plane crashed in the southern city of Rostov-on-Don, Russian officials said.
